    <h2>Benefits</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Get 50% off pay as you go adult <a href="/fares/find-fares">fares</a>&nbsp;to travel on bus, Tube, tram, DLR, London Overground, TfL Rail (excluding between West Drayton and Reading) and most National Rail services in London</li>
	<li>Buy and use a&nbsp;child rate 7 Day, monthly or longer period <a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/travelcards-and-group-tickets">Travelcard</a> or <a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/bus-and-tram-pass">Bus &amp; Tram&nbsp;Pass</a></li>
	<li>Buy discounted paper <a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/single-and-return-tickets">single or return tickets </a>from National Rail</li>
</ul>

<h2>Can I get it?</h2>

<p>You must be claiming:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Jobseekers Allowance or Universal Credit, be aged between 18-24 and unemployed for 13-39 weeks</li>
	<li>Jobseekers Allowance or Universal Credit, be aged 25 or over and unemployed for 13-52 weeks</li>
	<li>Incapacity Benefit, Employment and Support Allowance or Income Support and actively engaged with an adviser in returning to employment</li>
</ul>

<p>In the first few months of commuting to your new job, you may also&nbsp;be eligible for help with your fares. Contact your <a href="https://www.gov.uk/contact-jobcentre-plus">local Jobcentre Plus office</a> for more information.</p>

<h2>How to apply</h2>

<p>You need to go to your <a href="https://www.gov.uk/contact-jobcentre-plus">local Jobcentre Plus office</a> to apply.</p>

<h2>Start using your card</h2>

<ol>
	<li>Take your Jobcentre Plus photocard and Oyster card to any <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/oyster-ticket-stops">Oyster Ticket Stop</a> or Tube station</li>
	<li>Ask staff to add your Jobcentre Plus Travel Discount to your Oyster card. You need to give a password</li>
	<li>Add pay as you go credit to your Oyster card</li>
	<li>Create or sign in to your <a href="/fares/contactless-and-oyster-account">contactless and Oyster account</a> and add your Oyster card. Use the same password you gave to staff when they added your discount. If you don't, you can't get a refund or replacement</li>
	<li>Carry your photocard and Oyster card with you at all times</li>
	<li><a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/pay-as-you-go/touching-in-and-out">Touch in</a>&nbsp;at the start of your journey and&nbsp;<a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/pay-as-you-go/touching-in-and-out">touch out</a> at the end on yellow card readers</li>
	<li>Don't let anyone else use your cards</li>
</ol>

<h2>Expiry</h2>

<p>Your photocard is valid for three months.</p>

